The paper deals with brain image registration using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of probabilistic models and regularization techniques also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of deep neural networks implies a potential focus on neural networks (cs.NE) and the use of information theory (cs.IT) to capture transformation relationships at different levels.
